MEC Panyaza Lesufi will also address parents and staff of the school on Friday evening. JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Education Department will release its report into the death of  Parktown Boys' High pupil Enoch Mpianzi. The 8th grader drowned last week at a school camp. MEC Panyaza Lesufi will also address parents and staff of the school on Friday evening. In the meantime, Lesufi says schools planning any water related activities in Gauteng - will now have to get approval from the provincial education department.